The paper deals with the task of translating images between domains without prior knowledge in the form of correspondences, which is a common problem in computer vision. The paper proposes an alternative method to existing methods that apply adversarial learning to ensure that the distribution of the mapped source domain is indistinguishable from the target domain. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also introduces a non-adversarial mapping method that relies on a pre-trained generative model of the target domain, which suggests that the paper may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also presents extensive experiments validating the advantages of the proposed method, which suggests that the paper may also belong to the graphics (cs.GR) and multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories.
